OL,3,CMan jailed for 30 years after setting
OL,4,Cfire to victim's house whilst she slept
OL,6,FThe woman, who jumped out of a first-
OL,7,Ffloor window to safety, suffered two
OL,8,Fbroken ankles and a broken vertebrae
OL,9,Fin her back from the jump.
OL,11,FThe victim was initially woken in the
OL,12,Fmiddle of the night after hearing her
OL,13,Fletterbox snapping closed and then
OL,14,Fheard a crackling sound which
OL,15,Fresembled a log burner. Shortly after
OL,16,Fshe realised her house was ablaze and
OL,17,Fjumped out of her bedroom window to
OL,18,Fsafety.
