OL,3,CMan jailed for 30 years after setting
OL,4,Cfire to victim's house whilst she slept
OL,6,FAt the time of the offence, Martin was
OL,7,Fon bail for a previous assault with
OL,8,Fconditions in place for him not to
OL,9,Fcontact the victim and to reside in
OL,10,FLeicester. But he left his bail
OL,11,Faddress, rented a car and drove to
OL,12,FWorsley.
OL,14,FHe booked into a hotel and waited
OL,15,Funtil the middle of the night to carry
OL,16,Fout his attack when his ex-partner
OL,17,Fwould be asleep.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/17
