OL,3,CMan jailed for 30 years after setting
OL,4,Cfire to victim's house whilst she slept
OL,6,F"I have spent many months in trauma
OL,7,Ftherapy and clinical psychology
OL,8,Fsessions trying to develop strategies
OL,9,Fto manage the frequent flashbacks and
OL,10,Fnightmares of the fire. The chilling
OL,11,Fmemory of the clear thought that I was
OL,12,Fgoing to die, the choking feeling of
OL,13,Fsmoke inhalation, and the fall as I
OL,14,Fjumped out of the bedroom window, will
OL,15,Fnever leave me. I am plagued by
OL,16,Fintrusive thoughts of what would have
OL,17,Fhappened if there had been family
OL,18,Fmembers staying with me at my home.
OL,26,@nD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G10/17
